issues.title: ffserver is listed as running even when it isnt when checking status
issues.body:
e.g:

sowhat@Monk-RPC:/var/sunra/sunra_ffs_relay$ ps -edalf | grep ffserver
0 S sowhat   15079 19346  0  80   0 -  3986 pipe_w 14:30 pts/1    00:00:00 grep --color=auto ffserver

sowhat@Monk-RPC:/var/sunra/sunra_ffs_relay$ ./sunra_ffserver_relay.rb status
I, [2015-04-01T14:31:02.135927 #15086]  INFO -- : FFServer is Running!

commit.message: The command to delete the lock file prior to killing the pids had been incorporated into one of the comments
Sunra utils use github version now
Sunra utils use github version now
Some sanity edits - status was far too complex so I've split it up; lock_file pids are now delegated
ffmpeg_pipe may be blank OR ommited. Style changes. Renamed
Fixed Gemfile to use latest utils; renamed ffserver relay file
Reorganisation to allow for sunra_utils gem. Tidy up
About to refactor to use new utils collection

issue_comments.body: Looks like an issue with get_pid in sunra_utils
